Hazard type: Digital
Vector: Network
Danger: Non-lethal/Low disruption
Range: Limited


One World Story was a social media website that peaked in popularity between 2007 and 2008, eventually becoming defunct in 2014. Since approximately November 2016, the phrase &quot;One World Story&quot; will sometimes replace the text in the logomarks for existing social media websites during page load. Newer, virally popular websites are affected disproportionally. The mechanism of this phenomenon is not currently understood.

Filtering is not available at this time.

Click below to view a gallery of affected logomarks:

----------------------------------------

[https://staging.cohostcdn.org/attachment/d4ea0c6e-f8fd-4370-8365-fa30013b81e7/oneworldstory.svg]
